17 2021-04-20 vomiting Severe headache; Worst migraine; Excessive vomitting; Patient under 18 given vaccine; Hasn't felt we... Read more
Close
Severe headache; Worst migraine; Excessive vomitting; Patient under 18 given vaccine; Hasn't felt well; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of HEADACHE (Severe headache) and VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) in a 17-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 627A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (No reported medical history). Concomitant products included DULOXETINE, CLONIDINE, HYDROXYZINE, AMITRIPTYLINE, RAMELTEON and ETHINYLESTRADIOL, NORGESTIMATE (MONO LINYAH) for an unknown indication. On 16-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 08-Mar-2021, the patient experienced MALAISE (Hasn't felt well). On 16-Mar-2021, the patient experienced PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Patient under 18 given vaccine). On 08-Apr-2021, the patient experienced VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) (seriousness criterion medically significant). On 11-Apr-2021, the patient experienced HEADACHE (Severe headache) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and MIGRAINE (Worst migraine). On 08-Apr-2021, VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) had resolved. At the time of the report, HEADACHE (Severe headache), MIGRAINE (Worst migraine), PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Patient under 18 given vaccine) and MALAISE (Hasn't felt well) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On an unknown date, White blood cell count: elevated (High) Elevated. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. Patient was treated with fluids, Zofran, Benadryl, Tylenol 800mg and Aspirin for headaches. Company comment: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

18 2021-02-03 nausea For my first dose, I had quite mild symptoms. I woke up with a migraine the next morning and some so... Read more
Close
For my first dose, I had quite mild symptoms. I woke up with a migraine the next morning and some soreness at the injection site. Both of these lasted a couple of days and were able to be treated with over-the-counter pain medicine. My second dose, however, provided much worse flu-like symptoms. About 12 hours after I received the injection, I was woken with a migraine much worse than the first, nausea, chills, joint pain, sore throat, and fatigue. While the chills and nausea subsided, the other symptoms persisted until the next day. As of today (2/4/21), all symptoms are gone except for soreness at the injection site.

Close
Pt received vaccination at 1:30pm, pt ambulated to observation area, began feeling "dizzy and nauseous" while standing in observation area. Pt ambulated to chair, at which time pt lost consciousness and her body became stiff, gagging sounds noted. Removed pt's mask, applied oxygen at 10l/min via face mask. pt regained consciousness within 30 -60 seconds. Vital signs BP 124/82, unable to assess sp02 due to cold fingers and nail polish. HR 102. Pt stated she continued to feel dizzy, and had tingling in her fingers. Vital signs reassessed at 1:43, BP 128/78, HR 80, unable to asses sp02 due to monitor not giving a reading. Vitals reassessed at 1:46pm, sp02 100%, HR 94. , began titrating oxygen supply down by 2l/min. Pt seemed to tolerate well for a few minutes, At 2:00pm, pt complained of tingling returning to her fingers, pt was receiving o2 4l/min, sp02 noted at 80%, increased 02 to 10l/min, called nursing lead who called 911. 2:10, unable to obtain accurate sp02. 2:17pm pt continues to receive 02 10l/min, stated she "feels okay, just weird and foggy" no tingling in hands. 2:20pm, paramedics arrive, pt states she is "a little bit dizzy" 2:35pm pt taken to hospital via stretcher with paramedics. Pt en route to hospital. At 2:00pm sp02 80%

18 2021-03-16 nausea Approximately 7-8 minutes after receiving the vaccine, started to feel light-headed, thought she was... Read more
Close
Approximately 7-8 minutes after receiving the vaccine, started to feel light-headed, thought she was going to pass out, and her heart was racing extremely high. The health care team at the site took her blood pressure, measured heart rate, gave her water, juice and chocolate and tried to get her heart rate to drop. It was fluctuating up and down and she couldn't stand up without dizziness; we waited 45 minutes and then drove her home as she was unable to drive her own car. She was experiencing significant lightheadedness, and consistent heart racing even while lying down on the sofa/bed. This continued for several days and she stayed home from school and sports. We called her primary care doctor on the 10th and they suggested she wait another day to see how she was feeling. She started to feel a bit better by Friday, was still experiencing a bit of the tiredness, nauseous, light-headed and heart spikes, but was able to drive, move around. On Sunday evening, she started to experience increased heart rate again, lymph nodes were very painful and started experiencing the light headedness all evening. On Monday we took her to her primary care provider and they then referred her to ER for the heart racing and a EKG. The increased light headedness, feeling like she will pass out even while laying in bed, dizziness has all increased and her lymph nodes continue to be swollen and painful. It has been over a week since the vaccine and there is no clear sign of her reaction getting any better, if not worse. The EKG results indicated a new abnormality and we are trying to get her to a cardiologist. She is and had been a very healthy, varsity athlete that runs over 30 hours a week with track, and since receiving the first dose of the Moderna vaccine is unable to move very far within the house without feeling that she is going to pass out or that her heart rate is shooting up uncontrollably.

Difficulty swallowing; Shortness of breath; Big rash; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 18-year old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced events shortness of breath, difficulty breathing, tightness on the throat, difficulty swallowing, big rash in forehead and under her eyes. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant medications reported were birth control pill for drug use for unknown indication. On 9 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the events the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: unknown) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 9 Mar 2021, the patient experienced the event shortness of breath, difficulty breathing, tightness on the throat, difficulty swallowing, big rash in forehead and under her eyes. Treatment details included went to the emergency room (ER), epinephrine, diphenhydramine, and dexamethasone.. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of event, shortness of breath, difficulty breathing, tightness on the throat, difficulty swallowing, big rash in forehead and under her eyes was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Right eye twinching; lightheadedness; rash on hands; Nausea; DOB; This case was received via an unknown source (no reference has been entered for a health authority or license partner) on 10-Feb-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 11-Feb-2021. This spontaneous case was reported by a nurse (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of BLEPHAROSPASM (Right eye twinching), DIZZINESS (lightheadedness), RASH (rash on hands), NAUSEA (Nausea) and DYSPNOEA (DOB) in an 18-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 037K20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. I received an allergy immunotherapy shot the day before my first dose of the vaccine and instantly felt nauseous and extremely tired after receiving the vaccine, which continued for two days after receiving tut. Three days later, I woke up struggling to breathe (but not anaphylactic), covered in hives, itchy all over, shaking, disoriented, and chilled but not truly feverish. After my second dose, I feel just a bit tired and sore, so I think this truly was a bad reaction to the two injections combined rather than to the vaccine itself. Still, it was a debilitating experience, and I would recommend considering putting out guidance that other immunotherapy patients space out their allergy injections and vaccines farther than I did.

Fainting; Injection site soreness in arm; nauseous; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 21-year-old, female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced, fainting (syncope), injection site soreness in arm (vaccination site pain), and nausea (nausea). The patient's medical history included vasovagal condition that cause heart rate and blood pressure to drop due to stress on body and dehydration resulting in fainting. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 09 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 013M20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 09 Feb 2021, the patient was fine until about 11 pm after which she experienced arm soreness on the injection site and felt nauseous. On 10 Feb 2021, at 5 am in the morning, the patient fainted. The patient assumed that shot might have added stress to her body which most likely caused her to faint. No treatment information was provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. There was no change planned to the dosing schedule of mRNA-1273 in response to the event as patient would be receiving second dose on 09 Mar 2021. The outcome of events, fainted (syncope), injection site soreness in arm (vaccination site pain), and nauseous (nausea), were considered as unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the onset date of the reported events of syncope, vaccination site pain, and nausea, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Client received 1st Pfizer injection on 1/11/2021 at different facility. Client came to us to "start over" and my nurse signed off and vaccinated her with 1st Moderna vaccine on 3/24/2021. Close
Appendicitis; Stomach cramps; A spontaneous case report was received from a consumer concerning a 25 years old, female patient who had received Moderna's COVID-19 and experienced events as appendicitis, stomach cramps. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.. On 17 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (batch number: 047A21A) via Intramuscular route on Left Arm for COVID-19 infection prophylaxis. On 20 Mar 2021, the patient experienced stomach cramps. on 21Mar and was diagnosed to have Appendicitis and underwent appendicectomy on the same day. The patient was treated with Tylenol and Advil for stomach cramps. The event Appendicitis seriousness were considered as hospitalization and medically significant. The action taken with mRNA-1273, in response to events was unknown. The outcome of the events appendicitis and stomach cramps was not resolved at the time of this report.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 25 Y/O F hospitalized with a serious unexpected event of appendicitis and nonserious unexpected abdominal pain upper. Event onset 4 days after first dose mRNA-1273. Events ongoing. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

25 2021-05-10 nausea Approximately 10 minutes after the patient got her second moderna vaccine she became faint and dizzy... Read more
Close
Approximately 10 minutes after the patient got her second moderna vaccine she became faint and dizzy. The patient was sitting at the time. A law enforcement officer witnessed her becoming faint and ran over to attend her. I was called over to assess her as well. The law enforcement officer called EMS. The patient stated that she felt faint, dizzy, she said she had a headache, blurry vision, and was nauseous. The patient appeared sweaty and she appeared to loose consciousness briefly twice. She did not show any signs of redness, rash, or swelling. After sitting for a few minutes, and before EMS arrived, the patient said she was improving. She did not lose consciousness anymore but she still had a headache, nausea, and blurry vision. When EMS arrived they recommended that she get checked out at the emergency room, but the patient refused stating that she did not want to go to the hospital and that she was feeling better. The patient called her parents and they came and picked her up.
